Presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar, has assembled a legal team to challenge the victory of Bola Tinubu in the February 25 presidential election. The former vice-president briefed the team at his campaign headquarters in Abuja on Wednesday. He mandated them to establish the “claim of illegality in the February 25 presidential election and reclaim the mandate of the Nigerian people”. The team, which is headed by JK Gadzama, comprises 19 senior advocates of Nigeria (SANs). More subsequently…